cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about domain adaptation in neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions experiments with two language pairs, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the languages are related to image processing, and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) if the experiments involve neural network optimization.
